fields.value: Replication Data for: Gender Equality Mood Across States and Over Time

dsDescriptionValue.value: This article provides a new measure of state-level attitudes towards gender roles.  Our series, gender equality mood, spans from 1972 to 2010 and is the first measure to capture variation in gender role attitudes across states and over time.  The series is created using two leading techniques for opinion estimation: multi-level regression and poststratification and survey aggregation.  We conclude by discussing several research areas in which our measure of gender equality mood may be especially useful.

publicationCitation.value: Koch, Julianna, and Danielle M. Thomsen. 2017. “Gender Equality Mood across States and over Time.” State Politics & Policy Quarterly 17 (4): 351–60.

fields.value: This dataset underwent an independent verification process that replicated the tables and figures in the primary article. For the supplementary materials, verification was performed solely for the successful execution of code. The verification process was carried out by the Odum Institute for Research in Social Science at the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.
